This paper focuses on the detection of malware using machine learning techniques, specifically in the area of adversarial attacks on Domain Generation Algorithms (DGAs). This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses deep learning and random forest classifiers, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The use of side information to improve the robustness of the classifiers suggests a focus on network infrastructure (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE).
